    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York 208 Thompson St</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>April 22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 5618. 1858</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir/</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You will perceive by the enclosure the<lb/> principle cause of this
                correspondence with you<lb/> but at the same time I am glad of the<lb/> opportunity
                thus offered to write on other matters.<lb/> First then, How is it that no one ever
                calls or sends<lb/> to me for my indebtedness to the “Occident?„ If<lb/> I knew the
                amount I would <sic>sent</sic> it to you<lb/> next I should like you to acknowledge
                rect<lb/> of $25 which I presume you must have recd<lb/> nearly a year ago (I
                believe a donation to your<lb/> present Congregation.) please give me this<lb/>
                satisfaction by private correspondence as I<lb/> dislike all public display.——<lb/>
                <sic>trusting</sic> this will find you in the enjoyment<lb/> of good health &amp;
                happiness</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">I am as ever</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Yours sincerely Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Ansel<add>?</add> Leo</persName>
            </p>
            <p>To/</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">&amp;c &amp;c</p>
        </body>
    </text>
